<h2>Technical Information</h2>

<p>A complete description of the Sloan Digital Sky Survey scientific
program and instrumentation can be found in the <a
href="http://www.astro.princeton.edu/PBOOK/welcome.htm">SDSS Project
Book</a>.  There is <a href="tech_summary.html">an abbreviated
summary</a> of some of the principal attributes of the survey, which is
designed to be completed in five years of observations.  The SDSS
photometric system is calibrated using the <i>u'g'r'i'z'</i> magnitudes
of <a href="../documents/photo_primary_stds.html">these standard
stars</a>.</p>

